# AI Integration Rules

## LLM Usage
- Primary model: Google Gemini Pro (via `google-generativeai` SDK)
- Use streaming for all user-facing AI responses
- Track token usage and cost per call
- Implement retry with exponential backoff for API failures
- Always set temperature, max_tokens, and other parameters explicitly

## Prompt Engineering
- Store all prompts as template files in `backend/app/prompts/`
- Use `{variable_name}` syntax for template variables
- Every prompt has: system prompt + context injection + task instruction
- Include negative examples ("DO NOT...") for common failure modes
- Version prompts — track changes and rationale

## Buddi Persona Consistency
- All AI responses must follow the Buddi persona (see `docs/03-ai/PERSONA-BUDDI.md`)
- Warm, knowledgeable, opinionated but respectful
- Specific and actionable, never vague
- Honest about uncertainty
- Emoji usage: sparingly, purposefully (weather icons, activity icons, status indicators)

## RAG (Retrieval Augmented Generation)
- Use Chroma for vector storage (MVP)
- Embed knowledge chunks as standalone, self-contained pieces
- Retrieve top-5 relevant chunks per query
- Always include retrieved context in prompts — don't rely on LLM training data for destination facts
- Tag chunks with metadata (destination, category, attraction_id) for filtered search

## Structured Output
- For choice cards, itinerary data, condition assessments: request JSON output
- Validate AI-generated JSON against Pydantic schemas before using
- Handle malformed AI output gracefully (retry once, then fallback)

## Safety
- Never use AI-generated content for safety-critical decisions without data grounding
- Condition assessments must be based on actual API data, not AI hallucination
- Always cite data sources for weather, tides, and trail closures
- When AI doesn't know something, it must say so (never fabricate)

## Tool/Function Calling
- Define tools with clear descriptions and parameter schemas
- Tools are the bridge between AI and real data (weather, tides, attractions DB)
- Log all tool calls for debugging and cost tracking
